    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-08-21T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-08-21T15:00:00-05:00" n="633"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d633">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/1029: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Vladivostok</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CJK1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caldwell</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-08-21T16:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 21, 1919, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>For <persName corresp="#p_SCH1">Smith</persName>.</p>
                <p>Following from <persName corresp="#p_SJF1">Stevens</persName>: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“August 19, 4 p.m. Japanese General <persName>Oba</persName>, commanding
                            the railway guards <persName>Semenoff</persName> territory, tells
                            inspectors most decidedly he <pb facs="0685" n="573" xml:id="pg_573"/>
                            will not interfere with <persName>Semenoff</persName> as that would be
                            interference with Russian internal affairs. Everything points to a
                            combination <persName>Oba</persName>–<persName>Semenoff</persName> to
                            intimidate and prevent work, and antagonistic spirit more clearly
                            defined than ever. I have just ordered inspectors out of all
                                <persName>Semenoff</persName> territory as I consider lives in
                            danger.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Department regards such action should not be taken without approval of
                    Inter-Allied Committee and has so advised <persName corresp="#p_SJF1"
                        >Stevens</persName>. Please take up with <persName corresp="#p_SJF1"
                        >Stevens</persName> and with Committee and report result. Advise <persName
                        corresp="#p_MRS1">Morris</persName>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
